2026-03-05 07:49:41,378 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': "Replace EUI's jQuery EasyUI datagrid with a DUI equivalent: server-rendered table via +datagrid pug mixin (driven by JSON config files), backed by datagrid-plugin.js providing the full JS API (reload, load, loadData, getData, getRows, getSelected, getSelections, clearSelections, appendRow, updateRow, deleteRow, options), callbacks (onBeforeLoad, onLoadSuccess, onClickRow, onDblClickRow, onDeleteRow, onSelect, onUnselect, onBeforeSelect, onBeforeUnselect, onDblClickCell, onRowContextMenu), toolbar wiring via asdpx config, and auto-generated row editor modals. Page scripts must be able to call the same $.fn.datagrid methods they used under EUI — including selectRow, unselectRow, and selectRecord which are currently no-ops affecting 13+ pages."}
2026-03-05 07:49:47,259 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'Steps 1-19 complete (mixin, plugin core, JSON extraction, toolbar, editor modal, styler support).\n\nStep 20: Investigation — row click behaviour. Found selectRow/unselectRow/selectRecord are no-ops, dblclick editor fires before callback, missing EUI callbacks.\n\nRemaining row-click work (steps 21-24):\n- Step 21: Implement selectRow(jq, index) — highlight row, set state, fire onBeforeSelect/onSelect, enable toolbar, scroll into view\n- Step 22: Implement unselectRow(jq, index) — remove highlight, fire onBeforeUnselect/onUnselect, disable toolbar if no selection remains\n- Step 23: Implement selectRecord(jq, id) — find row by idField, delegate to selectRow\n- Step 24: Fix dblclick — fire onDblClickRow before editor open, add onDblClickCell, add onRowContextMenu, skip editor if onDblClickRow returns false'}
2026-03-05 07:49:50,642 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_done args={'number': 20}
2026-03-05 07:49:52,983 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Implement selectRow(jq, index) — EUI-compatible programmatic row selection'}
2026-03-05 07:50:01,935 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 21, 'text': "EUI selectRow(_a5) behaviour to replicate:\n1. Get row data by index — return if not found\n2. Fire onBeforeSelect(index, row) — return if false\n3. If singleSelect, clear all existing selections (unselectAll internally)\n4. Add 'dg-selected' class to the TR\n5. Update state.selectedRow / state.selectedIndex\n6. Fire onSelect(index, row)\n7. Scroll row into view (EUI has scrollOnSelect option, default true)\n8. Enable toolbar buttons\n\nAlso update bindRowSelection click handler to use this shared logic instead of inline code — DRY up the select/unselect path so click and programmatic selectRow behave identically.\n\nPages affected: wip_count (5 calls), physical_count (5 calls), resources_charts, resource_efficiency_chart, analysis, ticket, _wo_seq — 13+ call sites total."}
2026-03-05 07:50:05,402 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Implement unselectRow(jq, index) — EUI-compatible programmatic row deselection'}
2026-03-05 07:50:11,214 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 22, 'text': "EUI unselectRow(_a6) behaviour to replicate:\n1. Get row data by index — return if not found\n2. Fire onBeforeUnselect(index, row) — return if false\n3. Remove 'dg-selected' class from the TR\n4. Clear state.selectedRow / state.selectedIndex if this was the selected row\n5. Fire onUnselect(index, row)\n6. Disable toolbar buttons if no rows remain selected\n\nExtract shared _unselectRow() helper so both the click toggle-off path and the programmatic method use the same logic.\n\nPages affected: dg_filter.inc.js (line 119 — onSelect calls unselectRow to prevent selection), coc_man.js (line 117)."}
2026-03-05 07:50:14,248 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Implement selectRecord(jq, id) — find row by idField, delegate to selectRow'}
2026-03-05 07:50:19,309 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 23, 'text': 'EUI selectRecord behaviour:\n1. Read opts.idField from datagrid options\n2. Search state.data.rows for the row where row[idField] === id\n3. Get its index\n4. Delegate to selectRow(index)\n\nMust also support idField being set via JSON config or data attribute. Currently idField is not parsed from data attrs — may need to add data-id-field to parseDataAttrs().\n\nPages affected: ci_man.js (line 255 — autoload feature).'}
2026-03-05 07:50:23,379 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Fix dblclick — fire onDblClickRow before editor, add onDblClickCell + onRowContextMenu'}
2026-03-05 07:50:37,641 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 24, 'text': "Current bug: dblclick opens editor modal BEFORE firing onDblClickRow callback. Pages like dg_jobstat define onDblClickRow for navigation (loadpage) — they get both editor AND navigation.\n\nEUI dblclick flow (lines 671-686):\n1. Find clicked TR and resolve index/row\n2. Find clicked TD — fire onDblClickCell(index, field, value) if TD has a field\n3. Fire onDblClickRow(index, row)\n4. EUI does NOT auto-open editor on dblclick — that's page-specific behaviour\n\nFix in bindRowSelection dblclick handler:\n1. Fire onDblClickCell(index, field, value) if click target is inside a td[data-field]\n2. Fire onDblClickRow(index, row) — if it returns false, skip editor\n3. Only open editor if onDblClickRow did NOT return false AND no onDblClickRow was defined (auto-editor is DUI-specific convenience)\n\nAlso add contextmenu handler:\n- Bind 'contextmenu.dgSelect' on tbody tr\n- Fire onRowContextMenu(e, index, row)\n- e.preventDefault() only if callback is defined\n\nPages using onDblClickRow: _wo_bas.inc.js, dg_jobstat.js, cp_man.js (both versions)\nPages using onRowContextMenu: dg_jobstat.js (commented out xonRowContextMenu — but the callback should exist for future use)"}
