2026-03-05 08:10:55,862 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Fix click toggle — plain click always selects, only ctrl+click toggles (match EUI)'}
2026-03-05 08:11:04,642 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 25, 'text': "Bug: DUI click handler toggles selection on every click. Double-click fires click→click→dblclick, so second click unselects the row before dblclick fires. Row ends up unselected after double-click.\n\nEUI behaviour (lines 640-668):\n- ctrl/meta+click: toggle (select if unselected, unselect if selected)\n- shift+click: range select (clearSelections, select from lastSelectedIndex to current)\n- plain click: ALWAYS clearSelections + selectRow (never toggles off)\n\nFix in bindRowSelection click handler:\n1. Check e.ctrlKey / e.metaKey — only toggle on ctrl+click\n2. Check e.shiftKey — range select (can defer, not critical now)\n3. Plain click: if singleSelect, clear others then select. If already selected, no-op (don't unselect)\n4. This makes double-click safe: click1 selects, click2 is no-op (already selected), dblclick fires with row still selected"}
2026-03-05 08:13:18,214 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 25, 'id': 620, 'text': 'Bug: DUI click handler toggles selection on every click. Double-click fires click→click→dblclick, so second click unselects the row before dblclick fires. Row ends up unselected after double-click.\n\nEUI click handler (lines 620-668) fires ALL of these on every click:\n1. onClickCell(index, field, value) — if click target is inside td[field]\n2. Row selection (singleSelect: always select; ctrlSelect: ctrl=toggle, shift=range, plain=clear+select)\n3. onClickRow(index, row) — always fires\n\nFix in bindRowSelection click handler:\n1. Add onClickCell — find td[data-field], fire callback with (idx, field, value)\n2. singleSelect plain click: always _selectRow (never toggle off) — matches EUI line 636-637\n3. ctrl/meta+click: toggle (select if unselected, unselect if selected)\n4. shift+click: defer for now (not critical)\n5. onClickRow fires after selection, on every click (already correct)\n6. This makes double-click safe: click1 selects, click2 is no-op (already selected), dblclick fires with row still selected'}
