2026-03-05 08:36:39,213 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "## What to update\n\n### File: `docs/dui/datagrid.md`\n\n#### 1. Methods table (line ~200-215) — Add new selection methods:\n\n| Method | Args | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `selectRow` | index | Select row by index (fires onBeforeSelect/onSelect, scrolls into view) |\n| `unselectRow` | index | Unselect row by index (fires onBeforeUnselect/onUnselect) |\n| `selectRecord` | id | Select row by idField value (searches rows, delegates to selectRow) |\n\n#### 2. JSON config properties table (line ~30-43) — Add:\n\n| Property | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `idField` | String | — | Primary key field name (used by selectRecord to find rows) |\n\n#### 3. Callbacks table (line ~219-225) — Add new callbacks and update existing:\n\n| Callback | Args | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `onBeforeSelect` | index, row | Fires before selection; return `false` to cancel |\n| `onSelect` | index, row | Fires after a row is selected |\n| `onBeforeUnselect` | index, row | Fires before unselection; return `false` to cancel |\n| `onUnselect` | index, row | Fires after a row is unselected |\n| `onClickCell` | index, field, value | Fires on cell click (always, alongside onClickRow) |\n| `onDblClickCell` | index, field, value | Fires on cell double-click |\n| `onRowContextMenu` | e, index, row | Fires on right-click (context menu) |\n\nUpdate existing:\n- `onClickRow` — note: fires on every click, not just selection changes\n- `onDblClickRow` — note: return `false` to prevent editor from opening\n\n#### 4. Selection behaviour section (new, under Notes) — Document:\n- singleSelect: plain click always selects (never toggles), matching EUI\n- Multi-select: ctrl/meta+click toggles, plain click clears all + selects one\n- Double-click fires: onDblClickCell → onDblClickRow → editor (if no onDblClickRow or it didn't return false)\n- Click fires: onClickCell → selection logic → onClickRow (always)\n\n### File: ui_help tabs\nThe ui_help page (`html/dui/mod/dev/ui_help.js`) parses docs by `## headings` into tabs:\n- Overview, Mixins, Parameters, Examples, Output, JS API, Notes\nAll changes are within the markdown file — the ui_help tabs auto-populate from the `## JS API` and `## Notes` sections. No ui_help code changes needed.\n\n### CSS change documentation\nAlso add a note about the `.modal-box:has(table.table)` CSS rule (tight padding for modals containing datagrids) — this belongs in the Notes section."}
2026-03-05 09:07:39,167 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'toolbar-mixin', 'title': 'Implement reusable +toolbar mixin', 'steps': ['Create +toolbar and +toolbar-sep mixins in toolbar.pug', 'Add sandbox test cases in sbox_pac Toolbar tab', 'Verify toolbar renders correctly in browser', 'Refactor datagrid.pug to delegate to +toolbar']}
2026-03-05 09:07:45,831 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Extract the datagrid toolbar pattern into a standalone reusable +toolbar mixin. The mixin should produce identical output to the current datagrid toolbar (same CSS classes, same button structure, same filter field handling). The datagrid mixin will then delegate to +toolbar as the final step — single source of truth for toolbar appearance.'}
2026-03-05 09:07:58,312 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Implementation plan\n\n### Reference: datagrid.pug lines 58-101\nCurrent datagrid toolbar renders:\n- Container: `.flex.items-center.gap-1.px-2.py-1.bg-base-200.border-b.border-base-300`\n- Optional title: icon + text, flex-1\n- Optional filter fields: `+form` wrapper with `+fitem` children\n- CRUD buttons (asdpx): a=Add, e=Edit, d=Delete — disabled by default\n- Custom buttons: via `+button` mixin\n- Block content at end\n\n### Step 1: Create mixin\nAdd `+toolbar(opts)` to `html/dui/mixins/toolbar.pug` (below existing topnav mixins).\n- Attrs: id, title, icon, asdpx, justify\n- `+toolbar-sep` already exists as `+topnav-sep` CSS — reuse `.toolbar-sep` class\n- Filter fields and custom buttons via block content initially\n- asdpx buttons rendered from opts\n\n### Step 2: Sandbox test cases\nAdd examples in sbox_pac Toolbar tab:\n- Plain toolbar with custom buttons\n- Toolbar with asdpx CRUD buttons\n- Toolbar with title + icon\n- Toolbar with filter fields\n\n### Step 3: Verify in browser\nScreenshot comparison, ensure identical appearance to datagrid toolbar.\n\n### Step 4: Datagrid delegation (final)\nReplace datagrid.pug lines 58-101 with `+toolbar` call, passing same params. Verify no visual/functional regression on sa_parts and other pages.'}
