2026-03-05 09:32:10,617 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'Toolbar mixin renders 3 logical sections in a single flex row:\n\n1. **Title** (shrink-0) — icon + title text, fixed width\n2. **Inputs** (flex-1) — filter fields in a +form, stretch to fill\n3. **Buttons** (shrink-0) — CRUD (from asdpx) + custom buttons + separators, pack right\n\nJSON toolbar array items routed by type:\n- `type: "field"` → Inputs section as +fitem\n- `type: "sep"` → Buttons section as +toolbar-sep\n- no type / `type: "button"` → Buttons section as +button\n\nRender order in buttons section: CRUD buttons first, then JSON items (buttons + seps) in array order, then pug block content.\n\nSize property (`xs`/`sm`/`md`) controls button size class and container padding:\n- xs: btn-xs, py-1 (default, datagrid compact)\n- sm: btn-sm, py-1 (standalone toolbars)\n- md: btn-md, py-1.5 (prominent action bars)\n\nTitle section: shrink-0 (was flex-1, that moves to inputs form).\nPug block content renders in buttons section (same as now).'}
2026-03-05 09:32:15,982 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Toolbar 3-section layout, separators, and size property', 'description': 'Refactor +toolbar mixin to render 3 logical sections (title shrink-0, inputs flex-1, buttons shrink-0). Add separator support via { type: "sep" } in JSON and +toolbar-sep in pug block. Add size property (xs/sm/md) controlling button size class and container padding. Update sandbox test cases to demonstrate separators and sizes. Update JSON test config with separator example.'}
