2026-03-05 10:17:34,912 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'devmenu-overrides', 'title': 'Dev Menu Overrides — add/override system menus with migration status', 'steps': ['Design new devmenu.json schema', 'Update injectDevMenu() in lib/pages.js', 'Apply overrides during filterTree in lib/routes/api.js', 'Update nav-plugin.js buildMenu to render status indicators', 'Update Pug menu mixin for server-side render path', 'Create devmenu.json with real migration status data', 'Browser verify — sidebar shows status dots', 'Update docs']}
2026-03-05 10:17:41,132 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Replace `data/devmenu.json` with a new schema that supports two capabilities:\n1. **Add** new menu groups (replaces current dev menu injection)\n2. **Override** properties on any existing system menu item — keyed by item ID\n\nPrimary use case: show DUI migration status (red/amber/green) on each page in the sidebar nav, so developers can see at a glance which pages are migrated, in-progress, or not started.\n\nOnly active when `$.isdev` — production menus are never affected.'}
2026-03-05 10:17:55,557 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Architecture\n\n### Data flow\n1. `data/devmenu.json` loaded at startup by `lib/pages.js` (cached in `_devMenu`)\n2. At `/api/init` time, `injectDevMenu()` handles the `add` array (same as today but from new schema)\n3. During `filterTree()` in `api.js`, after `Object.assign({}, node)`, merge any matching override properties onto the copy\n4. Client receives enriched menu items with optional `status`, `badge`, `cls` properties\n5. `buildMenu()` in nav-plugin.js reads these and renders visual indicators\n\n### New JSON schema\n```json\n{\n  "add": [\n    { "id": "dev", "text": "Development", "icon": "icon-dev", "children": [...] }\n  ],\n  "override": {\n    "inv^sa_parts": { "status": "green", "badge": "DUI" },\n    "inv^gate_pass": { "status": "amber" },\n    "inv^sa_stock": { "status": "red" }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Override properties\n- `status` — "green" | "amber" | "red" — rendered as a small coloured dot before the menu text\n- `badge` — optional short text badge after the menu text\n- `cls` — optional CSS class(es) added to the menu `<a>` element\n- Any other property merges onto the node (e.g. override `text`, `icon`)\n\n### Key files\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `data/devmenu.json` | New schema with `add` + `override` |\n| `lib/pages.js` | Update `getDevMenu()` → `getDevMenuConfig()`, return full config object |\n| `lib/routes/api.js:52-54,70-82` | Pass overrides into filterTree, merge during copy |\n| `nav-plugin.js` buildMenu | Read `status`/`badge`/`cls`, render dot/badge |\n| `html/dui/mixins/nav.pug` | Same for server-side render path |\n\n### Constraints\n- Override merge happens on the COPY, never mutates `global.$.menus`\n- Only active when `$.isdev` — the override map is never loaded in production\n- Backward compatible — if devmenu.json is still old format (has `id` at top level), treat it as a single add item'}
2026-03-05 10:18:01,818 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 1, 'text': "Define the JSON schema for `data/devmenu.json`:\n- `add`: array of menu group objects (same structure as today's single object, but now an array)\n- `override`: object keyed by menu item ID, values are property overrides\n- Backward compat: if file has `id` at top level (old format), wrap as `{ add: [oldObj], override: {} }`\n- Write the schema definition, not the actual data file yet (that's step 6)"}
2026-03-05 10:18:07,469 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 2, 'text': 'Update `lib/pages.js`:\n- Rename `getDevMenu()` → `getDevMenuConfig()` — returns the full parsed JSON (not just a single menu node)\n- Add backward compat: if parsed JSON has `id` at top level, wrap as `{ add: [parsed], override: {} }`\n- Update `injectDevMenu(menus, udata)` to iterate `config.add` array instead of single object\n- Export `getDevMenuConfig()` so api.js can access overrides separately\n- File: `lib/pages.js:114-145`'}
2026-03-05 10:18:13,540 1095779 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': 'Update `lib/routes/api.js:48-88`:\n- After calling `injectDevMenu()`, get the override map from `getDevMenuConfig().override`\n- In `filterTree()` at line 75, after `Object.assign({}, node)`, check if `overrides[node.id]` exists\n- If so, `Object.assign(copy, overrides[node.id])` — merges status/badge/cls onto the copy\n- This is safe because filterTree already copies each node — no mutation of global.$.menus\n- Recurse into children so nested overrides work too'}
