2026-03-05 16:16:28,855 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_project_set args={'description': 'File-level versioning, locking, changelog generation, and build tooling for mcpp. Replaces pure-git.\n\n**Critical**: A CLI (puredev replacement) is required — this is both an MCP tool module AND a standalone CLI tool.\n\n**Architecture decisions**:\n- Git commit messages are the single source of truth — no database\n- Per-file metadata stored as pipe-delimited lines in commit body (full body parsing via `--format=%H%n%B`)\n- Build tooling should use modern tools (esbuild/swc/ruff etc), not legacy uglify-es/clean-css\n- Binary compilation uses Node.js 20+ Single Executable Applications (SEA), not pkg/nexe'}
2026-03-05 16:16:33,706 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'commit-format', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': "Per-file pipe lines go in commit body (not subject). Multiple files per commit. Parse with `git log --format=%H%n%B` for full body access — NOT --oneline/--grep which only sees subjects. Version auto-increment from last known version in git history. Backward-compatible with pure-git's single-line-per-commit format (infoParse handles both old and new). Reference: pure-git fileCommit() in git.js:204-226, infoParse() in git.js:416-468."}
2026-03-05 16:16:36,945 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'file-operations', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'All file queries use full body parsing (`git log --format=%H%n%B`), not --grep/--oneline. dev_file_show parses git log bodies for matching pipe lines. dev_file_list scans all commits. Lock/unlock creates a commit with L flag set/cleared in pipe line. dev_file_locked scans for latest L flag per file. Locked files blocked from dev_commit. May use runtime cache (not DB) to avoid re-parsing within a session.'}
2026-03-05 16:16:40,045 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'rebuild-from-git', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'With no DB, this task becomes a verification/audit tool. Scans full git history with body parsing, validates pipe-line integrity, reports any inconsistencies (e.g. version gaps, orphaned locks). Could also serve as a migration tool to parse old pure-git format (pipe in subject line) alongside new format (pipe in body).'}
2026-03-05 16:16:43,999 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'build-system', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': "Modern tooling replaces pure-git's legacy stack:\n- JS minification: esbuild or swc (not uglify-es)\n- CSS minification: esbuild or lightningcss (not clean-css)\n- Pug compilation: keep pug CLI or find Python equivalent\n- Binary compilation: Node.js 20+ Single Executable Applications (SEA) built-in — replaces pkg/nexe\n- Three-repo model (source → target → binary) preserved from pure-git\nReference: pure-git puredev.js comBuild/comRelease, minify.js, config.json."}
2026-03-05 16:16:46,788 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'changelog', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'dev_changelog queries git log with full body parsing (`--format=%H%n%B`), extracts pipe-delimited lines, filters by file/task/date/version. Default output is markdown grouped by file. Also supports pipe-delimited output (format="pipe") for backward compatibility. Runtime cache may speed up repeated queries within a session.'}
2026-03-05 16:16:50,048 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'cli', 'kind': 'plan', 'text': 'Python CLI replacement for puredev. Commands mirror pure-git: build/dev, release, info, locked/lock/unlock, changelog, validate, findFile/findText, tree. CLI calls the same core functions used by MCP tool handlers. All git queries use full body parsing. Binary compilation via Node.js 20+ SEA. Modern build tools (esbuild/swc/lightningcss). Reference: pure-git puredev.js switch(_cmd) at line 1072.'}
2026-03-05 16:18:09,347 1149856 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'build-system', 'kind': 'note', 'text': 'SEA path migration: pure3 code using `__dirname`/`__filename` needs updating for SEA. Use `process.execPath` or `import.meta.dirname` for path resolution. Assets must be declared in SEA config JSON and accessed via `node:sea` API (`sea.isSea()`, `sea.getAsset()`). No virtual filesystem — cleaner than pkg but still requires adaptation. Each platform needs its own build (no cross-compilation).'}
