2026-03-05 17:49:04,756 1177280 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Architecture Decision: Server-Rendered Column Chooser\n\nThe datagrid mixin already reads the JSON config — it knows every column and its `coloff` flag. The column chooser dropdown should be **server-rendered in pug** as a `+menubutton` in the datagrid toolbar, with checkbox menu items for each column that has a `title`.\n\n### Pug mixin (datagrid.pug) renders:\n- A `+menubutton` (e.g. "Columns" with a columns icon) in the toolbar area\n- Checkbox `<li>` for each column with a `title` (skip hidden-only/checkbox cols)\n- `coloff:true` columns → unchecked by default\n- Other columns → checked by default\n- Each item has `data-field="FIELD_NAME"` for the plugin to wire\n\n### Plugin JS only needs to:\n1. Wire checkbox click → toggle `display:none` on matching th/td by `data-field`\n2. On init, read localStorage for saved prefs, apply them (override pug defaults)\n3. On toggle, persist to localStorage keyed by `pageId + \'^\' + gridId + \'^cols\'`\n\n### Why this is better than EUI:\n- EUI builds the entire dropdown in JS (`$(\'<div class="colpan">\'), $(\'<ul>\'), $(\'<li>\')...`) — violates DUI\'s server-rendered-first principle\n- DUI renders the structure in pug, JS only handles interaction + persistence\n- The `columns` method stub in the plugin becomes a thin wiring function, not a DOM builder\n\n## EUI Reference (eui.extend.js)\n\n### `columns` method (line 1674)\n- Called by page scripts: `dg.datagrid(\'columns\', $(\'#dgre_tb\'))`\n- Reads cookie for saved column visibility\n- If no cookie: builds default list excluding `coloff:true` columns (line 1689)\n- Renders checkbox list, each toggle calls `showColumn`/`hideColumn`\n- Saves to cookie on every toggle\n\n### `showColumn` / `hideColumn` (line 1755-1766)\n- jQuery EasyUI built-in methods — show/hide columns by field name\n- DUI has these as stubs (no-ops) at lines 1110-1114\n\n### `formedit` editor modal (line 2097-2118)\n- Only `editor` property matters — `coloff` and `hidden` irrelevant\n- All columns with `editor` → visible fitem; without → hidden input\n- DUI already handles this correctly\n\n## Affected Files\n- `html/dui/mixins/datagrid.pug` — render menubutton column chooser in toolbar\n- `public/dui/js/plugins/datagrid-plugin.js` — wire toggle, showColumn/hideColumn, localStorage\n- JSON configs with coloff: sa_sorder_solines, sa_ship_shiplines, quote_man_qlines\n- 20+ page scripts call `.datagrid(\'columns\', ...)` — will become thin wiring'}
