2026-03-06 09:49:27,278 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_list args={}
2026-03-06 09:49:36,189 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'fitem-ssot', 'title': 'Fitem restructure — single source of truth CSS variable + uniform DOM structure', 'steps': ['Define --east-west-w CSS variable and derive --fitem-label-w', 'Replace hardcoded fitem width with var(--east-west-w) + max-width guard', 'Update .two/.three/.four grid columns to use --east-west-w', 'Update +vsplit() default to use --east-west-w', 'Restructure fitem DOM — uniform slots (label, body, prefix, input, suffix)', 'Auto-adjusting input width — input shrinks when suffix icons/buttons present', 'Verify toolbar fitems unaffected — opt-out from standard sizing', 'Verify modal fitems follow standard rules', 'Visual verification — sandbox page + real pages (sa_parts, wo_bas)']}
2026-03-06 09:49:46,436 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Replace all hardcoded fitem/form sizing with a single CSS variable `--east-west-w: 25em` that drives: west panel width, fitem width, label width, and grid column sizing. Restructure fitem DOM to have uniform slots (label, body, prefix, input, suffix) so inputs auto-shrink when suffix buttons/icons are present. Result: change one variable, everything scales consistently. Current hardcoded values (24rem fitem, 8rem label, 400px vsplit) must produce identical visual output after refactor.'}
2026-03-06 09:49:54,866 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Single source of truth: `--east-west-w: 25em`\n\n### Derived values\n- `--fitem-label-w: calc(var(--east-west-w) * 0.32)` → 8em (matches current 8rem)\n- fitem `width: var(--east-west-w)` → replaces hardcoded 24rem\n- fitem `max-width: calc(var(--east-west-w) + Nem)` → guard for unconstrained containers\n- `+vsplit()` default → uses `--east-west-w` when no arg provided\n- `.two/.three/.four` grid columns → fitems sized by variable, max-content works naturally\n\n### DOM restructure\nEvery fitem gets uniform slots:\n```\n.fitem\n  label\n  .fitem-body        (flex row for everything after label)\n    .fitem-prefix    ($ sign, icon — often empty)\n    input/select/textarea\n    .fitem-suffix    (buttons, icons, bool-dot — often empty)\n```\nInput fills space between prefix and suffix via flex.\n\n### Context overrides\n- Toolbar fitems: explicitly opt out (width:auto, label:auto, compact) — already in components.css\n- Modal fitems: assumed to follow standard rules — verify during step 8\n\n### Key files\n- `public/dui/css/forms.css` — variable definitions, fitem sizing, grid rules\n- `public/dui/css/components.css` — toolbar fitem overrides\n- `html/dui/mixins/form.pug` — fitem mixin DOM structure\n- `html/dui/mixins/layout.pug` — vsplit mixin'}
2026-03-06 09:50:00,336 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 1, 'text': 'Add `--east-west-w: 25em` to `:root` or `form` in forms.css. Replace `--fitem-label-w: 8rem` with `--fitem-label-w: calc(var(--east-west-w) * 0.32)`. Verify computed values match current (25em = 400px, 0.32 * 25em = 8em ≈ 128px). This is the foundation — everything else derives from this.'}
2026-03-06 09:50:02,739 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 2, 'text': 'Replace `.fitem { width: 24rem }` with `width: var(--east-west-w)`. Add `max-width: calc(var(--east-west-w) + Nem)` as guard for unconstrained containers (modals, standalone forms). The N value TBD — probably 2-3em. Keep `max-width: 100%` so it still respects narrow containers.'}
2026-03-06 09:50:04,321 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': '`.two/.three/.four` use `max-content` for non-last columns. Since fitem width is now `var(--east-west-w)`, max-content will automatically pick up the correct width. Verify grid columns size correctly — each non-last column should be ~25em wide, last column fills remainder.'}
2026-03-06 09:50:07,070 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 4, 'text': "In layout.pug `+vsplit()` mixin: when no width argument is provided, default to `var(--east-west-w)` instead of requiring every page to pass '400px' or '25em'. Pages that pass explicit values still override. This eliminates inconsistent widths across 80%+ of pages."}
2026-03-06 09:50:11,670 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'text': 'Restructure fitem mixin in form.pug to output uniform DOM:\n```\n.fitem\n  label (existing)\n  .fitem-body (new flex wrapper)\n    .fitem-prefix (new — for $ prefix, icons; empty when unused)\n    input/select/textarea (existing)\n    .fitem-suffix (new — for buttons, bool-dot, icons; empty when unused)\n```\nThis is the biggest change — all 105+ pages render fitems through this mixin. The suffix slot replaces ad-hoc button placement. CSS for .fitem-body uses flex so input fills space between prefix and suffix.'}
2026-03-06 09:50:13,316 1284678 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': 'CSS for the new structure: `.fitem-body { display: flex; flex: 1; min-width: 0; }` — input gets `flex: 1` to fill available space. When .fitem-suffix contains buttons/icons, the input automatically shrinks. Suffix uses `flex-shrink: 0` so buttons maintain their size. This replaces any manual width calculations.'}
