2026-03-07 10:10:23,647 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'css-cleanup', 'title': 'CSS cleanup — eliminate patch-on-patch conflicts', 'steps': ['Audit and document all conflicting rules (DONE — see goal note)', 'Redesign panel-body/tab-content spacing system (replace margin-on-children with clean approach)', 'Eliminate !important usage in sidebar.css, tree.css, components.css where possible', 'Consolidate 18-selector grid column margin-top into single rule', 'Clean up combobox width:0 hack and tab-icon zero-width hack', 'Fix readonly field styling (pick one signal: opacity OR dashed border)', 'Verify all pages after changes (sa_parts, quote_man, consol, admin pages, tool_request)']}
2026-03-07 10:10:33,355 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'name': 'css-cleanup', 'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Eliminate the "patch on patches" pattern across all DUI CSS files. The current system has accumulated conflicting rules over a month of incremental fixes — rules setting values then subsequent rules undoing them, !important escalation to escape @layer, zero-width hacks, and 18-selector redundancy.\n\n## Audit findings (15 conflicts identified)\n\n### Critical\n1. Vertical tabs !important margin war — layout.css vs components.css\n2. Combobox select width:0 hack — flex:1 contradicted by width:0, JS fixes it\n3. Tree checkbox 3× !important — beating broken DaisyUI v5 24px default\n4. Tree expand arrow !important — hiding DaisyUI chevron from outside @layer\n5. Sidebar collapsed !important inconsistency — one rule uses it, sibling doesn\'t\n\n### High\n6. Form input sizing outside @layer — escaping cascade to beat DaisyUI\n7. 18 grid column margin-top selectors — copy-paste redundancy\n8. Tab icon zero-width container — width:0 height:0 overflow:visible hack\n9. Readonly field: opacity AND dashed border — conflicting visual signals\n10. Body font-size hidden cascade — html:16px → body:0.8125rem → inherit\n\n### Medium\n11. Select focus outline-offset — undoing DaisyUI double-border\n12. Panel/tab child margins — assumes direct children, breaks with wrapper divs (sa_parts bug)\n13. Textarea .spec overrides standard min-height\n14. Toolbar fitem max-width:none override\n15. Sidebar collapsed text hiding — inconsistent !important\n\n### Key pages to verify after any changes\nsa_parts, quote_man, consol, admin/events, dqm/gauge_tx, tool_request'}
