2026-03-07 15:24:53,147 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'note', 'text': '## Searchbox Filter Drawer — Design Decision\n\n### Context\nThe searchbox needs column-level filtering, similar to EUI\'s qbedef.js pattern where each column can have an `editor` (textbox, combobox, datebox, numberbox) that sends additional query params to the server endpoint.\n\n### Chosen Design: Left slide-out drawer\nA filter panel slides out from the left edge of the dropdown when a filter/funnel icon is toggled. Results table stays fully visible while filtering.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ ◁ Filters       │ Part ID │ Description │ Class │ UOM │ ...   │\n│                 ├─────────┼─────────────┼───────┼─────┼───────┤\n│ Part Class      │ A8000   │ Widget...   │ COMP  │ EA  │ ...   │\n│ [All________▼]  │ A8001   │ Gadget...   │ FG    │ EA  │ ...   │\n│                 │ ...     │             │       │     │       │\n│ Traceable       │         │             │       │     │       │\n│ [All________▼]  │         │             │       │     │       │\n│                 │         │             │       │     │       │\n│ Product Code    │         │             │       │     │       │\n│ [____________]  │         │             │       │     │       │\n│       [Apply]   │         │             │       │     │       │\n└─────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Why not filter row in thead?\n- Cramped with narrow columns (UOM 60px, Class 80px)\n- Dropdown-inside-dropdown is awkward UX\n- qbedef has more filter fields than display columns (ALIAS_DESC, USER_1-5, DIM_TRACKED) — can\'t fit in table\n\n### Why left drawer?\n- Results stay fully visible — user sees filter effect immediately\n- Proper form layout with labels using existing +fitem() mixin\n- Combobox/datebox editors get full-width inputs, not crammed into cells\n- Consistent with DUI styling patterns\n\n### JSON Config\nAdds a `filters` array to searchbox JSON config, using same editor format as qbedef.js:\n```json\n"filters": [\n  { "field": "PART_CLASS_ID", "title": "Part Class", "editor": { "type": "combobox", "options": { "data": [...] } } },\n  { "field": "TRACEABLE", "title": "Traceable", "editor": { "type": "combobox", "options": { "data": [...] } } },\n  { "field": "PRODUCT_CODE", "title": "Product Code", "editor": "textbox" },\n  { "field": "ALIAS_DESC", "title": "Alias", "editor": "textbox" }\n]\n```\n\n### Implementation Rules\n- **Server-side first**: Filter drawer DOM is built by pug mixin using +fitem() or equivalent\n- **Use existing mixins** where available and workable\n- JS only wires events: toggle drawer open/close, collect filter values, add to queryParams on search\n- Filter icon (funnel) toggles the drawer — sits in the thead or status bar\n- Drawer has `base-200` background, smooth CSS transition for slide animation\n- Combobox editors become native `<select>` or DUI combobox depending on complexity\n- Clicking Apply (or Enter in a filter field) re-queries with filter params added to queryParams'}
2026-03-07 15:25:01,289 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Filter drawer — JSON config & pug mixin', 'description': 'Add `filters` array support to searchbox JSON config (same editor format as qbedef.js). Update the +searchbox() pug mixin in input.pug to server-render the filter drawer DOM: a `.searchbox-filters` panel with +fitem() or compact label/input pairs for each filter, a funnel toggle icon, and an Apply button. Use existing DUI mixins where workable. The drawer is hidden by default, toggled via CSS class.'}
2026-03-07 15:25:08,031 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Filter drawer — CSS styling & slide animation', 'description': 'Add CSS to searchbox.css for the left slide-out filter drawer: base-200 background, fixed width (~220px), smooth CSS transition (transform/width), proper z-index layering alongside the results table. The dropdown becomes a flex row when filters are open: drawer on the left, results on the right. Funnel icon styling, active filter indicator.'}
2026-03-07 15:25:14,408 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Filter drawer — JS event wiring', 'description': 'Wire up the filter drawer in searchbox-plugin.js: toggle open/close on funnel icon click, collect filter field values on Apply (or Enter), merge filter params into queryParams for doSearch(), clear filters button. No DOM construction in JS — only event binding and value collection on server-rendered elements.'}
2026-03-07 15:25:21,711 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Filter drawer — test JSON config & visual verification', 'description': 'Add filters to sbox_pac_BD_SEARCH.json matching the EUI part qbedef pattern (Part Class combobox, Traceable combobox, Product Code textbox, etc.). Rebuild plugins + CSS, test in browser: toggle drawer, apply filters, verify server query includes filter params, verify results narrow correctly. Screenshot verification.'}
