2026-03-07 19:06:31,389 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Server-side combo cache in endpoints.js\n\n### Architecture\n- Cache layer wraps `apiRequest()` inside `processSqlIdRequest()`\n- Only caches `_combo=y` GET requests — dropdown list loads\n- Write ops (`_func=upd/ins/del`) NEVER cached\n- In-memory Map (clears on pm2 restart — natural invalidation)\n\n### Cache tiers by data volatility\n| Tier | TTL | sqlids |\n|------|-----|--------|\n| static | 24h | admin^curr, admin^gst |\n| slow | 30min | inv^pn_partclass, vwltsa^depid1, vwltsa^shiftid, vwltsa^resourceid, dqm^gaugeType, dqm^department |\n| medium | 5min | vwltsa^custid, inv^vendorid, inv^partid (default for _combo=y) |\n| never | 0 | QBE searches, anything without _combo=y, write ops |\n\n### Cache key\n`_sqlid` + sorted non-underscore query params (to differentiate filtered combos)\n\n### Invalidation\n- On successful write (upd/ins/del) for a module → bust all cache entries for that module prefix\n- e.g. save new customer → clear all `vwltsa^*` cache entries\n- pm2 restart clears everything\n\n### Configuration\nTier rules in config.yaml under `combo_cache:` with `default_ttl`, `tiers`, and per-sqlid `rules`\n\n### Implementation\n~20 lines in endpoints.js: check cache before apiRequest(), store on success, bust on write. No client-side changes needed.'}
