2026-03-07 19:21:30,496 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Server-side combo cache in endpoints.js\n\n### Architecture\n- Cache layer wraps `apiRequest()` inside `processSqlIdRequest()`\n- Only caches `_combo=y` GET requests — dropdown list loads\n- Write ops (`_func=upd/ins/del`) NEVER cached\n- In-memory Map (clears on pm2 restart — natural invalidation)\n\n### Self-tuning adaptive cache\nEach cached entry tracks:\n- `hash` — MD5/simple hash of response body\n- `data` — cached response\n- `cachedAt` — timestamp\n- `refreshCount` — total remote fetches\n- `changeCount` — times hash differed from previous\n- `lastChanged` — timestamp of last actual change\n\n**Change ratio** = changeCount / refreshCount → drives adaptive TTL:\n| Ratio | Meaning | Adapted TTL |\n|-------|---------|-------------|\n| 0.00 | Never changes | 60min (cap) |\n| < 0.02 | Rarely changes | 60min (cap) |\n| < 0.10 | Changes occasionally | 30min |\n| ≥ 0.10 | Changes often | 5min |\n\n**Hard cap: 60 minutes** — even stable data gets revalidated hourly.\n\n### Round-robin background refresh\n- Every user combo request is served instantly from cache\n- One background refresh per request, cycling through entries whose adaptive TTL has expired\n- Entries that are still fresh are skipped in the rotation\n- Self-optimising: busy data checked often, stable data left alone\n\n### Cache key\n`_sqlid` + sorted non-underscore query params (to differentiate filtered combos)\n\n### Invalidation\n- On successful write (upd/ins/del) for a module → bust all cache entries for that module prefix\n- e.g. save new customer → clear all `vwltsa^*` cache entries\n- pm2 restart clears everything\n\n### What is NOT cached\n- Non-combo requests (no `_combo=y`)\n- Write operations (upd/ins/del)\n- QBE search results (filtered/paginated)\n\n### Configuration\nZero config needed — adaptive TTL learns from data. Optional overrides in config.yaml if needed.\n\n### Implementation\n~40 lines in endpoints.js:\n1. Before apiRequest(): check cache, serve if fresh\n2. After serving: if round-robin index points to an expired entry, background refresh it\n3. On refresh: hash-compare, update stats, recalculate TTL\n4. On write success: bust module cache entries\n\n### Future (parked)\n- Server-rendered combo data in initial page HTML, updated by AJAX later'}
