2026-03-07 19:27:43,480 1549321 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '## Server-side combo cache — lib/cache.js + lib/endpoints.js\n\n### Architecture\n- `lib/cache.js` — standalone cache module, in-memory Map\n- Integration in `lib/endpoints.js` wrapping `apiRequest()` for `_combo=y` GET requests\n- Write ops (`_func=upd/ins/del`) NEVER cached\n- Clears on pm2 restart — natural invalidation\n\n### Self-tuning adaptive cache\nEach cached entry tracks:\n- `hash` — MD5 of response body\n- `data` — cached response\n- `cachedAt` — timestamp\n- `refreshCount` — total remote fetches\n- `changeCount` — times hash differed from previous\n- `lastChanged` — timestamp of last actual change\n\n**Learning period**: First 5 refreshes use conservative 60s base TTL.\nAfter learning, change ratio = changeCount / refreshCount drives adaptive TTL:\n| Ratio | Meaning | Adapted TTL |\n|-------|---------|-------------|\n| 0.00 | Never changes | 5min (cap) |\n| < 0.02 | Rarely changes | 5min (cap) |\n| < 0.10 | Changes occasionally | 2.5min |\n| >= 0.10 | Changes often | 60s (base) |\n\n**Hard cap: 5 minutes** — even stable data gets revalidated.\n\n### Round-robin background refresh\n- Every cache hit triggers one background refresh of an expired entry\n- Cycles through entries round-robin, skipping fresh ones\n- Self-optimising: busy data checked often, stable data left alone\n\n### Cache key\n`_sqlid` + sorted non-underscore query params\n\n### Invalidation\n- On successful write for a module → bust all `module^*` cache entries\n- pm2 restart clears everything\n\n### Integration points in endpoints.js (~20 lines)\n1. Before apiRequest(): check cache for _combo=y GETs, serve if hit + trigger tick\n2. After apiRequest(): store response + fetchPath for background refresh\n3. On successful write: invalidateModule(module)\n\n### Future (parked)\n- Server-rendered combo data in initial page HTML, updated by AJAX later'}
