2026-03-08 08:28:26,076 1737642 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': '**Implementation plan:**\n\n1. **searchbox-plugin.js — template build** (where columns → th/td):\n   - When building the dropdown table header and row template, if a column has `autoHide: true`, add `coloff` class to both the `<th>` and the template `<td>`.\n\n2. **searchbox-plugin.js — row render loop**:\n   - Maintain a Set of column indices that are still hidden (`autoHideSet`).\n   - On each row iteration, for columns still in the Set, check if the cell value is non-empty.\n   - If non-empty: remove `coloff` from that column\'s `<th>` and all existing `<td>` cells via `nth-child(N)`, then remove the index from the Set.\n   - Once the Set is empty, skip all further checks (early exit).\n\n3. **searchbox.part.json** — add `"autoHide": true` to UDF and other optional columns (ALIAS_DESC, USER_1–USER_5, etc.).\n\n4. **Reset on new search** — when a new search is triggered, re-add `coloff` to autoHide columns and rebuild the Set, since different search results may have different populated columns.\n\n**Uses existing `coloff` class** from datagrid convention — no new CSS needed.'}
