2026-03-08 09:30:57,207 1737642 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'text': "## Root Cause\n\nSearchbox `selectItem` (searchbox-plugin.js:480) checks `opts.fields && opts.fields.length` before doing fkey load. But `searchbox.part.json` has no `fields` array, so the fkey branch is **never entered**. Falls through to `populateFields` which also exits immediately (no fields). Result: no form data loaded, no state transition, no toolbar update.\n\n## Combobox chain (working)\n1. `onSelect` (combobox-plugin.js:836) → `formLoad()`\n2. `formLoad` (line 482-507) builds URL: `/?_func=get&_sqlid=<form._sqlid>&<name>=<value>`\n3. `$frm.form('load', url)` → AJAX GET → server returns **full record**\n4. `loadData()` populates ALL fields → `onLoadSuccess()` → transition(VIEW) → `applyState()` → `butEn('adx')`\n\n## Searchbox chain (broken)\n1. `selectItem` → `opts.fields` undefined → fkey branch skipped\n2. `populateFields` → no fields → exits\n3. `$(el).trigger('change')` → only dirty tracking, no form load\n4. No server round-trip, no state transition, no toolbar update\n\n## Fix\nReplace the fkey handling (lines 480-493) with combobox-style formLoad:\n```js\nif ($el.hasClass('fkey') && $frm.length) {\n  isFkeyLoad = true;\n  var name = $el.attr('name');\n  var sqlid = $frm.attr('_sqlid');\n  if (sqlid && name && value) {\n    var url = '/?_func=get&_sqlid=' + sqlid + '&' + name + '=' + encodeURIComponent(value);\n    if (typeof getapp === 'function') {\n      try { url += '&_vpath=' + getapp(); } catch (e) {}\n    }\n    $frm.form('load', url);\n  }\n} else if (opts.fields && opts.fields.length) {\n  populateFields(el, row);\n}\n```\nKeep `fields`/`populateFields` for non-fkey searchboxes."}
