2026-03-08 09:59:04,928 1737642 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 4, 'text': "## Investigation: comboLazyLoad proper data flow\n\n### Failed approaches (reverted)\n1. Read $.dui.debug.comboLazyLoad in dataloader on document.ready — FAILS because /api/init hasn't returned yet\n2. Bake data-combo-lazy attr into body tag via Pug — REJECTED by user as a hack that circumvents established system\n\n### Key findings\n- /api/init sends `debug: global.$.debug` (from remote Pure3d admin^_globs), NOT `config.debug` (local config.yaml)\n- config.yaml debug flags are server-only (proxy, jsonRead, pageServe) — never sent to client\n- dataloader preloadCombos runs on window.load, BEFORE /api/init completes\n- $.page.startup() is called AFTER /api/init populates $.dui — this is the correct lifecycle hook\n\n### Correct implementation plan\n1. **api.js**: Merge config.debug.comboLazyLoad into the debug payload sent to client:\n   `debug: Object.assign({}, global.$.debug || {}, { comboLazyLoad: config.debug?.comboLazyLoad ?? false })`\n2. **dataloader-plugin.js**: Remove window.load combo preload. Instead expose preloadCombos so it can be called externally.\n3. **_startup.js or page-plugin.js**: After $.page.startup() (when $.dui is populated), trigger combo preloading with lazy/eager based on $.dui.debug.comboLazyLoad\n4. Keep dui:contentloaded handler in dataloader for panel refresh after navigation\n\n### Reverted files\n- layout.pug: body tag restored to plain `body`\n- dataloader-plugin.js: useLazy hardcoded back to `false`\n- config.yaml: comboLazyLoad set to `false` (flag kept for future use)"}
