2026-03-08 11:34:39,741 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Add searchbox reload method — qbe compatibility', 'description': "Implement `searchbox('reload', query?)` so qbe-compatibility shim can map `qbe('reload')` to searchbox. Method should reuse current query when no arg is provided, start from page 1, and respect updated `options().queryParams` and active filters."}
2026-03-08 11:34:45,828 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 13, 'text': "Compatibility target: `qbe('reload')` currently re-queries using current options/queryParams and optional search text. `searchbox('reload', query?)` should call internal search path (`doSearch`) with `_page=1` and `_rows=pageSize`, using `state._lastQuery` or input value when query is omitted.\n\nAcceptance checks:\n1. `$('#ID').searchbox('reload')` refreshes with latest `options().queryParams` mutations.\n2. `$('#ID').searchbox('reload', 'abc')` runs a new query immediately (no debounce delay) and updates `_lastQuery`.\n3. Works for load-more flow after reload (subsequent more starts at page 2).\n4. Does not break existing onLoadSuccess/onLoadError/onSelect callbacks.\n\nFollow-up: after reload method is in place, qbe shim can map methods: reload/select/loadForm/options/getValue/setValue/clear/enable/disable/readonly/destroy."}
2026-03-08 11:35:21,133 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_switch args={'name': 'qbe'}
2026-03-08 11:35:47,629 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Add qbe→searchbox compatibility alias shim', 'description': 'Create a compatibility layer so existing `$.fn.qbe(...)` calls can route to `searchbox` where supported, minimizing page-level rewrites while QBE is deprecated.'}
2026-03-08 11:35:56,919 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': "Alias design (investigated):\n\n1) Keep `$.fn.qbe` as entrypoint, but when element is searchbox-owned (`$.data(el,'searchbox')` or `eui='searchbox'`), proxy qbe calls to `$.fn.searchbox`.\n\n2) Method mapping:\n- `qbe('options')` -> `searchbox('options')`\n- `qbe('getValue')` -> `searchbox('getValue')`\n- `qbe('setValue', v)` -> `searchbox('setValue', v)`\n- `qbe('clear')` -> `searchbox('clear')`\n- `qbe('enable'|'disable'|'readonly'|'destroy')` -> same searchbox methods\n- `qbe('select', v)` -> setValue + trigger change\n- `qbe('loadForm', v)` -> setValue + trigger change\n- `qbe('reload', q?)` -> `searchbox('reload', q?)` (requires reload method in searchbox plugin)\n\n3) Init-object mapping (`$('#id').qbe({...})`):\n- Map `defid` to searchbox config key (`sbref`) and initialize searchbox options from corresponding JSON/definition.\n- Preserve `queryParams`, `valueField`, `onSelect`.\n- Special map: `sales_ids` -> `sorder`.\n\n4) Known incompatibility to handle explicitly:\n- Existing page pattern `qbe('options').dlog.dg.datagrid('reload')` has no searchbox equivalent; must be replaced by `searchbox('reload')` after mutating `queryParams`.\n\nAcceptance checks:\n- Legacy pages using `qbe('getValue'/'setValue'/'loadForm'/'select'/'reload')` continue working on searchbox controls.\n- `onSelect(rec)` still fires with selected row object.\n- Query param mutation + reload works without using `.dlog.dg` internals."}
2026-03-08 11:40:35,600 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': "Additional compatibility requirement:\n\nFor searchbox-backed elements, `qbe('options')` should return a facade object that preserves legacy access patterns used by pages:\n- `options.queryParams` must proxy to real `searchbox('options').queryParams` (mutable).\n- `options.dlog.dg.datagrid('reload')` must be shimmed to call `searchbox('reload')`.\n\nPurpose: avoid immediate page rewrites in files that currently do:\n`qbe('options').queryParams...; qbe('options').dlog.dg.datagrid('reload');`\n\nConstraint: keep facade minimal (only fields/methods required by current call sites), and mark as deprecated in comments."}
2026-03-08 11:41:46,388 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 6, 'text': 'Rollout/revert strategy requirement:\n\nImplement alias as a feature-flagged wrapper so we can switch or revert safely.\n\nProposed shape:\n1. Preserve current implementation as `$.fn.qbeLegacy` (or equivalent internal ref).\n2. Redefine `$.fn.qbe` as dispatcher:\n   - If alias flag OFF -> call legacy path unchanged.\n   - If alias flag ON and element is searchbox-backed -> route to searchbox compatibility facade.\n   - Otherwise -> fall back to legacy path.\n3. Single runtime toggle (e.g. `window.duiFlags.qbeAliasToSearchbox`) with clear default.\n4. Add deprecation comments + temporary telemetry logs for routed calls (optional debug mode).\n\nGoal: zero-risk rollback without page rewrites.'}
