2026-03-08 14:39:55,993 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_new args={'name': 'editable-contract', 'title': 'Global editable contract — class + API semantics across components'}
2026-03-08 14:40:02,051 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'goal', 'text': 'Define and implement a single, cross-component `editable` contract in DUI so `editable(false)` has consistent behavior without relying on `readonly`, and can be applied uniformly across input-like widgets (textbox/combobox/searchbox/datebox/etc.).'}
2026-03-08 14:40:02,102 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'kind': 'plan', 'text': '1) Define the editable contract and state matrix (`editable`, `readonly`, `disabled`) including precedence and expected UX.\n2) Introduce a shared class/state token (e.g. `.dui-noedit`) and base CSS rules for non-editable visual state.\n3) Implement `editable()` support in core plugins using the shared contract; avoid regressions in existing readonly/disabled logic.\n4) Update parser/defaults so `editable:false` in data-options/config initializes correctly.\n5) Validate on representative pages and publish migration guidance for existing code paths.'}
2026-03-08 14:40:06,429 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Define editable state contract and precedence', 'description': 'Document canonical behavior for `editable`, `readonly`, and `disabled` across DUI widgets, including event-level expectations (typing, dropdown open, programmatic set/get).'}
2026-03-08 14:40:09,863 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 2, 'text': 'Define matrix and precedence:\n- `disabled:true` = fully inactive (no focus/click/typing), highest precedence.\n- `readonly:true` = field participates in readonly/business-state behavior; plugin-specific readonly semantics remain intact.\n- `editable:false` = user cannot manually type/edit text, but control is not disabled; allow controlled interactions per widget contract.\n\nOutput artifact: concise reference table for all core widgets and agreed precedence order.'}
2026-03-08 14:40:16,066 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'Introduce shared .dui-noedit state class and base CSS', 'description': 'Add global CSS/state rules for non-editable visuals and interaction constraints without conflating with readonly or disabled styles.'}
2026-03-08 14:40:19,170 1861664 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': 'Define CSS tokens for `.dui-noedit` on input-like controls:\n- visual cue distinct from readonly/disabled\n- cursor behavior for non-typable state\n- optional pointer handling scoped to text-entry surface only (not whole widget) to avoid breaking dropdown/buttons.\n\nKeep rule generic so plugins can toggle one class consistently.'}
