2026-03-09 07:30:28,058 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 2, 'text': 'For each eui.extend.js category, read the corresponding DUI plugin and check for equivalent functionality:\n\n- form-plugin.js ↔ Form (parseOptions, defaults, methods — lines 316-622)\n- combobox-plugin.js ↔ Combobox (parseOptions, defaults, methods — lines 965-1658)\n- datagrid-plugin.js ↔ Datagrid (methods, defaults, editors, view — lines 1672-2620)\n- modal-plugin.js ↔ Dialog/Window defaults and parseOptions\n- Check for: tabs, tree, validation rules, textbox focus handling, multibox widget\n- Check eui.aliases(), eui.table(), eui.nav() utilities in bundle.js / DUI namespace'}
2026-03-09 07:30:34,083 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 3, 'text': "Produce a classification table for every override in eui.extend.js. Each entry gets one of three labels:\n\n1. **Already in DUI** — equivalent exists in a DUI plugin (note which plugin and where)\n2. **Not needed in DUI** — EUI-specific plumbing (parser hooks, EasyUI widget API shims) that DUI architecture eliminates\n3. **Missing, needs porting** — business logic or behaviour that DUI pages rely on but hasn't been ported yet\n\nFocus areas likely to have gaps:\n- Custom validation rules ($.fn.validatebox.defaults.rules)\n- Combobox pre-parser logic (extensive data-attribute parsing)\n- Datagrid custom editors and inline editing behaviour\n- Multibox widget (entirely custom, may need a DUI equivalent)\n- eui.aliases() if any DUI pages use data-alias"}
