2026-03-09 07:55:27,457 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 5, 'id': 666, 'text': "## Classification — Tabs\n\n### ALREADY IN DUI\n- tabs.methods.enableAll — tabs-plugin.js:186. Enables all tabs.\n- tabs.methods.disableAll — tabs-plugin.js:196. Disables all tabs except optional index. Slightly different signature (EUI takes idx to select, DUI takes idx to exclude) but same intent.\n\n### NOT NEEDED IN DUI\n- tabs.defaults.onUpdate — Translates tab titles (eui.translate) + enables buttons (butEn). Translation is EUI i18n not used in DUI. Button state is handled by toolbar-plugin.js.\n- tabs.defaults.onUnselect — Prevents switch if locked + manages button state. Lock part is needed (see below), button part handled by toolbar-plugin.\n\n### POTENTIALLY NEEDED — ASSESS LATER\n- tabs.methods.lock/unlock — Prevents tab switching via locked flag. DUI tabs-plugin has enableTab/disableTab per-tab but no global lock flag. Could be useful for edit-in-progress scenarios. **Low priority** — pages can use disableAll(0) to achieve same effect.\n- tabs.methods.onDemand — Lazy-loads tab content from <template> on first select. DUI doesn't have this. **Could be useful** but no DUI page currently uses lazy tabs. Defer until needed.\n\n### VERDICT\nCore tab enable/disable already ported. Lock/unlock and onDemand are potentially useful but not currently needed by any DUI page. No immediate porting required — revisit when a DUI page needs lazy tabs or tab locking."}
