2026-03-09 08:03:32,826 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'text': '## Final Audit Summary — eui.extend.js → DUI Plugin Coverage\n\nAudited ~130 EUI overrides across 12 component categories (2985 lines).\n\n### Overall Counts\n| Status | Count | % |\n|---|---|---|\n| ✅ Already in DUI | ~90 | 69% |\n| ❌ Not needed in DUI | ~34 | 26% |\n| ⚠️ Missing / Gap | ~6 | 5% |\n\n### Gaps Identified (all low priority)\n\n1. **Linkbutton double-click debounce** (Step 7) — EUI has click-lock pattern preventing rapid double-clicks. DUI button-plugin lacks this. Low risk — could add if needed.\n\n2. **Combobox first/last auto-select** (Step 11) — EUI nav buttons auto-select first/last item on boundary. DUI nav wraps around instead. Behavioural difference, not a bug.\n\n3. **Combobox find/selectKey** (Step 11) — EUI has `find(value)` and `selectKey(key)` methods. DUI combobox lacks these but `exists()` + `select()` cover most use cases.\n\n4. **Datagrid readonly toggle** (Step 12) — EUI has `readonly(bool)` to toggle entire grid editability. DUI datagrid lacks this but tbarEnable/tbarDisable + row editor controls achieve similar effect.\n\n5. **Datagrid toExcel** (Step 12) — EUI has `toExcel()` for CSV export. DUI datagrid lacks this. Could port if needed — straightforward utility.\n\n6. **Tree formatter with cls/count** (Step 13) — EUI tree formatter wraps node text in `.cls` span and appends `(count)` badge. DUI tree formatter is plain `node.text`. Page scripts can override.\n\n### Per-Step Breakdown\n| Step | Component | ✅ | ❌ | ⚠️ |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | Global Utilities | 12 | 7 | 0 |\n| 3 | Panel | 1 | 1 | 0 |\n| 4 | Dialog/Window | 2 | 1 | 0 |\n| 5 | Tabs | 4 | 2 | 0 |\n| 6 | Form | 16 | 0 | 0 |\n| 7 | Linkbutton | 0 | 1 | 1 |\n| 8 | Date/Time | 4 | 4 | 0 |\n| 9 | Number/Spinner | 1 | 1 | 0 |\n| 10 | Textbox/Validation | 9 | 7 | 0 |\n| 11 | Combobox | 17 | 11 | 2 |\n| 12 | Datagrid | 6 | 14 | 2 |\n| 13 | Tree/Multibox | 10 | 6 | 1 |\n\n### Conclusion\nDUI plugin system already covers ~95% of what eui.extend.js provides. The 6 gaps are all low priority and can be ported individually if/when a migrated page needs them. No blocking issues for migration.', 'kind': 'note'}
2026-03-09 08:09:20,498 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'text': '## Classification Basis & "Not Needed" Rationale\n\nThe "not needed" classifications fall into these categories:\n\n### 1. EUI plumbing that DUI doesn\'t need (architecture difference)\nThese are hacks to make EUI behave how DUI works natively:\n- **Parser hooks** ($.parser.onComplete, parseOptions for dialog/switchbutton) — DUI uses data attributes + parser-plugin, no EUI parser\n- **Panel loadingMessage** — DUI doesn\'t have EUI\'s panel loading overlay\n- **Dialog bodyCls \'dbox\'** — EUI styling hook, DUI uses native `<dialog>`\n- **Combobox onShowPanel/onHidePanel clicked flag** — EUI panel tracking, DUI uses native `<select>`\n- **Combobox onResize icon/sticky/refresh** — EUI panel resize hooks, not applicable to native select\n- **Combobox paginate/_paginate** — EUI infinite scroll in panel, DUI loads all options\n- **Combobox sticky group headers** — EUI panel scrolling, native select handles groups\n- **Combobox cloneFrom** — EUI panel cloning hack, DUI can share data arrays directly\n- **Combobox toCombo/toText** — EUI mode switching between combo/text, DUI handles via editbox differently\n- **Datagrid onBeforeLoad URL building** — EUI builds URL from _sqlid attr, DUI uses data-options\n- **Datagrid onBeforeEndEdit/onBeforeOpen** — EUI hook points, DUI has own lifecycle\n- **Datagrid label editor** — EUI custom editor type, DUI uses plain HTML in cells\n- **Datagrid view.onAfterRender sort class** — EUI CSS hook, DUI styles columns differently\n- **Datagrid editButs** — EUI button show/hide by name, DUI uses tbarEnable/tbarDisable\n- **Datagrid editDone/editFocus** — EUI row edit wrappers, DUI rowEditor handles internally\n- **Datagrid editAppend** — EUI row append with $autonum, DUI appendRow handles this\n- **Datagrid formedit/rowedit/enableCellEdit** — EUI edit modes, DUI has rowEditor pattern\n- **Datagrid dialog/resizeColumn** — EUI-specific dialog builder and column resize\n- **Datagrid showRows** — EUI filter-by-visibility, DUI uses loadData filtering\n- **Validatebox deltaX** — EUI tooltip positioning, DUI uses different validation display\n- **Textbox setValidType/dropbox** — EUI textbox wrappers, DUI inputs handle natively\n- **ValidateBox required/editable methods** — EUI dynamic flag setting, DUI uses HTML attributes directly\n\n### 2. Business logic that belongs in page scripts, not framework\n- **Linkbutton onClick dispatch** (but_add/but_clr) — page-specific button handlers\n- **Tree onCheck ajax persist** — page-specific server persistence\n- **Combobox .edit class inline dialog** — page-specific CRUD on combo items\n- **Combobox filtertip** — page-specific filter UI\n\n### 3. Commented-out / dead code\n- $.parser.onComplete — commented out\n- dialog.parseOptions — commented out\n- switchbutton.defaults — commented out\n- validatebox focus handler — commented out\n- validate parser — commented out\n\n### 4. Features where DUI equivalent covers the use case differently\n- **Combobox .first/.last auto-select** — classified as gap (⚠️), DUI nav wraps instead\n- **Tree move** — DUI has insert(before/after), page scripts can combine pop+insert\n- **Tree setIcon/clearIcon** — DUI tree update() handles iconCls\n- **Numberbox set** — DUI numberbox options set via standard jQuery plugin pattern\n- **Timespinner defaults** — DUI timespinner has own sensible defaults\n- **Datebox _sharedCalendar** — EUI optimisation, DUI uses native date input\n- **Datebox onChange pre/postdate** — DUI uses HTML min/max attributes on date inputs\n\n### 5. Multibox — NEEDS REVIEW ⚠️\nClassified 3 items as "not needed" because DUI uses native `<select multiple>`:\n- **striped/columns layout** — EUI renders checkbox grid, DUI uses native select. If pages need the visual grid layout, this IS a gap.\n- **onChecked event** — DUI uses native change event, but if page scripts depend on the onChecked signature/behaviour, may need a shim.\n- **separator config** — DUI hardcodes comma separator. If any page uses a different separator, this is a gap.\n\nThese classifications need validation against actual page usage to confirm.', 'kind': 'note'}
2026-03-09 08:27:39,569 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_notes_set args={'text': '## Page Usage Validation (actual grep of html/eui/mod/ and html/dui/mod/)\n\n### Items classified "not needed" but ACTUALLY USED in page scripts (8):\n\n| Item | Uses | Pages |\n|---|---|---|\n| `combobox(\'sticky\')` | 2 | sa_jobman (EUI+DUI) |\n| `combobox(\'toCombo\')` | 2 | part_trans (EUI+DUI) |\n| `combobox(\'toText\')` | 2 | part_trans (EUI+DUI) |\n| `datagrid(\'editDone\')` | 2 | capor_inc (EUI+DUI) |\n| `datagrid(\'rowedit\')` | 2 | wo_seq.inc (EUI+DUI) |\n| `eui.toolbar()` | 2 | dg_resutil (EUI+DUI) |\n| `eui.table()` | 16 | multiple pages across sales, inv, vwltsa |\n| `onResize` callbacks | 7 | multiple pages (panel/combobox config) |\n\n**These need one of:** DUI equivalent method, deprecation shim, or migration-map entry.\n\n### Items classified "not needed" and CONFIRMED UNUSED (28):\n`combobox(\'cloneFrom\')`, `combobox(\'paginate\')`, `combobox(\'filtertip\')`, `combobox(\'append\')`, `combobox(\'find\')`, `combobox(\'selectKey\')`, `combobox(\'delete\')`, `combobox(\'empty\')`, `datagrid(\'editButs\')`, `datagrid(\'editFocus\')`, `datagrid(\'editAppend\')`, `datagrid(\'formedit\')`, `datagrid(\'editCell\')`, `datagrid(\'enableCellEdit\')`, `datagrid(\'dialog\')`, `datagrid(\'showRow\')`, `datagrid(\'hideRow\')`, `datagrid(\'findRows\')`, `datagrid(\'showRows\')`, `datagrid(\'resizeColumn\')`, `validatebox(\'required\')`, `validatebox(\'editable\')`, `textbox(\'setValidType\')`, `textbox(\'dropbox\')`, `eui.eventOff()`, `eui.eventOn()`, `eui.colsort()`, `eui.droplist()`\n\n**These are truly not needed — no page calls them.**', 'kind': 'note'}
