2026-03-09 10:00:48,960 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'combobox-plugin: aliases (find, toText, toCombo, sticky, required)', 'description': 'Add alias/noop methods to combobox-plugin.js for methods that DUI already handles under different names'}
2026-03-09 10:01:03,738 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 14, 'text': "## Methods to add to combobox-plugin.js\n\n### find(jq, param)\n- Page calls: `combobox('find', {value:nv})` — part_trans:792\n- DUI equivalent: `exists(val)` — same logic\n- Implementation: add `find` to methods, extract value from param object, delegate to `exists`\n- Response dependency: YES — return value drives an `if` branch (duplicate trace warning)\n\n### toText(jq)\n- Page calls: `combobox('toText')` — part_trans:206\n- DUI equivalent: `editbox()` — switches to free-text mode\n- Implementation: alias toText → editbox()\n- Response dependency: YES — page expects free-text input after call\n- Note: EUI toText also removes inList validation — verify editbox does same\n\n### toCombo(jq)\n- Page calls: `combobox('toCombo')` — part_trans:207\n- DUI equivalent: `editbox(true)` — switches back to combo mode\n- Implementation: alias toCombo → editbox(true)\n- Response dependency: YES — page expects combo dropdown after call\n\n### sticky(jq)\n- Page calls: `combobox('sticky')` — sa_jobman:943\n- DUI equivalent: none — native select has no scrollable panel\n- Implementation: noop method (prevents crash)\n- Response dependency: NO — fire-and-forget chained call\n\n### required(jq, val) — via combobox/textbox delegation\n- Page calls: `combobox('required')`, `textbox('required')` — part_trans:199, 478\n- DUI equivalent: validatebox already has `required()` method\n- Implementation: add `required` to combobox.methods that delegates to validatebox('required')\n- Response dependency: NO return, but validation won't apply if missing — silent_fail\n\n## YAML items to update on completion\n- combobox_find → status: already\n- combobox_toText → status: already\n- combobox_toCombo → status: already\n- combobox_sticky → status: already (noop)\n- validatebox_required → status: already"}
2026-03-09 10:01:11,384 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'combobox-plugin: filtertip implementation', 'description': "Implement combobox('filtertip') — filter tooltip with checkboxes that modify query params and save to cookies. Highest-impact missing method (13 DUI pages)."}
2026-03-09 10:01:24,157 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 15, 'text': "## combobox('filtertip') — 13 DUI pages\n\n### What it does (EUI)\nCreates a tooltip/popover attached to a combobox with checkboxes that:\n1. Display filter options (e.g. status values: OPEN, CLOSED, PENDING)\n2. Check/uncheck modifies query params on the combobox's URL reload\n3. Saves selections to cookies so they persist\n4. Has a `default` array for initial checkbox state\n\n### Pages using it\ncp_man, sa_sorder, quote_item_man, inv/cp_man, coc_man, qp_phosman, qp_everslik, rent_man, gauge_inv, qp_coatman, ncr_main.inc (13 total)\n\n### Implementation approach\n1. Read EUI eui.extend.js filtertip implementation (~lines to find)\n2. Study the calling pattern from one page (e.g. rent_man:612)\n3. Implement as a method in combobox-plugin.js\n4. DUI approach: could use DaisyUI dropdown or popover instead of EUI tooltip\n5. Cookie persistence: use putcook/getcook pattern already in DUI\n\n### Response dependency\nNO — fire-and-forget setup call. But if it doesn't work, combobox loads ALL data instead of filtered subset.\n\n### YAML on completion\n- combobox_filtertip → status: already"}
2026-03-09 10:01:28,852 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'combobox-plugin: .first/.last parseOptions', 'description': 'Add .first/.last class support to combobox init — auto-select first or last item on load'}
2026-03-09 10:01:35,886 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 16, 'text': '## .first/.last class on combobox\n\n### What it does\nEUI: if combobox has class `.first`, auto-select first item on loadSuccess. If `.last`, auto-select last item.\n\n### Pages using it\nNeed to grep for usage — was flagged as missing but pages not yet scanned.\n\n### Implementation\nAdd to combobox-plugin init: check for .first/.last class, on loadSuccess select first/last option.\n\n### YAML on completion\n- combobox_parseOptions_first_last → status: already'}
2026-03-09 10:01:41,705 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'datagrid-plugin: readonly + editButs + editDone', 'description': 'Add datagrid methods for edge-case page control: readonly(bool), editButs(opts), editDone(). These are escape hatches for the ~5-10% of pages that need to override standard asdpx behaviour.'}
2026-03-09 10:01:56,048 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 17, 'text': "## datagrid edge-case control methods\n\n### readonly(jq, bool) — 5 DUI pages\n- rent_man:219,226 — lock/unlock datagrid when status CLOSED\n- release:10,13 — lock/unlock on release status\n- purchase_receipt:170,178 — lock/unlock receipt lines\n- Implementation: when true, disable all tbar buttons + prevent row editing. When false, re-enable per asdpx.\n- Uses internal tbarEnable/tbarDisable which already exist\n\n### editButs(jq, opts) — 3 DUI pages\n- rent_man:608 — `{add:'hide', edit:'hide'}` — permanently hide buttons\n- purchase_receipt:686,687 — `{ok:'click'}` — simulate click on save button\n- Opts pattern: `{buttonName: 'hide'|'show'|'enable'|'disable'|'click'}`\n- Implementation: find button by ID convention (`dgId_add`, `dgId_edit` etc), apply action\n- Note: 'ok' maps to save/endEdit — need to understand EUI pattern\n\n### editDone(jq) — 1 DUI page\n- capor_inc:17 — called on window open to end any active row editing\n- DUI has endEdit(idx) and validateRow(idx) separately\n- Implementation: find current editing row index, validateRow + endEdit\n- Response dependency: NO — fire-and-forget in onOpen callback\n\n### YAML on completion\n- datagrid_readonly → status: already\n- datagrid_editButs → status: already\n- datagrid_editDone → status: already"}
2026-03-09 10:02:00,854 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'datagrid-plugin: row visibility (findRows, hideRow, showRow, showRows)', 'description': 'Add row visibility methods to datagrid-plugin.js — client-side row filtering without reloading data'}
2026-03-09 10:02:12,407 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 18, 'text': "## Row visibility methods — 9 page calls across 5 DUI pages\n\n### findRows(jq, criteria) — 3 pages\n- purchase_order_list (vwltsa + inv):104,123,128 — find rows by LINE_STATUS\n- Returns `{rows: [...], idxs: [...]}` — matched rows and their indices\n- Implementation: iterate getRows(), match key-value criteria, return matches + indices\n\n### hideRow(jq, idx) — 3 pages\n- purchase_order_list:105,124,129 — hide closed/released lines\n- dg_resutil:173 — hide inactive resources\n- Implementation: find TR by index, set display:none\n\n### showRow(jq, idx) — 1 page\n- dg_resutil:172 — show selected resources\n- Implementation: find TR by index, set display:''\n\n### showRows(jq, criteria) — 2 pages\n- task_todo:290 — filter by TOBY_ME\n- ci_man:124 — filter by SRC_TYPE\n- Returns counts (visible/hidden)\n- Implementation: iterate rows, show matching, hide non-matching, return counts\n\n### Pattern\nAll four methods work together: findRows locates rows, hideRow/showRow toggle individual rows, showRows is a bulk filter. All operate on DOM visibility without changing the underlying data.\n\n### YAML on completion\n- datagrid_findRows → status: already\n- datagrid_hideRow → status: already\n- datagrid_showRow → status: already\n- datagrid_showRows → status: already"}
2026-03-09 10:02:17,952 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'datagrid-plugin: resizeColumn + toExcel', 'description': 'Add resizeColumn (1 page) and toExcel export (1 page) to datagrid-plugin.js'}
2026-03-09 10:02:26,313 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 19, 'text': '## resizeColumn + toExcel\n\n### resizeColumn(jq, {field, width}) — 1 page\n- prodexc:374 — resizes columns dynamically based on data\n- Implementation: find th/td by data-field, set width style\n- Response dependency: NO — fire-and-forget\n\n### toExcel(jq) — 1 page\n- sa_jobsched:315 — export schedule to Excel\n- EUI approach: builds HTML table → base64 data URI → download link\n- Implementation: read getRows() + column config, build CSV or HTML table, trigger download\n- Could use modern approach (Blob + URL.createObjectURL) instead of base64 data URI\n\n### YAML on completion\n- datagrid_resizeColumn → status: already\n- datagrid_toExcel → status: already'}
2026-03-09 10:02:31,472 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'tree-plugin: move, setIcon, formatter enhancements', 'description': 'Add tree methods: move (pop+insert wrapper), setIcon (update wrapper), and enhance formatter for cls wrapping and count badges'}
2026-03-09 10:04:55,141 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_task_status args={}
2026-03-09 10:05:07,382 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 20, 'text': "**tree-plugin: move, setIcon, formatter enhancements**\n\nItems from euiextend.yaml:\n- `tree_move` (status: missing, action: implement) — 1 page: `admin/js/menus.js:246`\n  - EUI: `tree('move', {target, point:'before|after'})` — reorder nodes\n  - DUI tree-plugin has `insert({before|after}, data)` but no `move` which relocates existing node\n  - Implementation: `move({target, point})` → remove node from current position, insert at new position\n  - Impact: hard_error — page drag-drop reorder breaks without it\n\n- `tree_setIcon` (status: missing, action: implement) — 1 page: `admin/js/menus.js:227`\n  - EUI: `tree('update', {target, iconCls:'icon-xxx'})` — set node icon\n  - DUI tree-plugin `update({target, iconCls})` already supported per docs!\n  - **Verify:** re-read tree-plugin update method — if iconCls is handled, this is `already` not `missing`\n  - If not handled: add iconCls support to update method\n\n- `tree_clearIcon` (status: not_needed, action: none) — no pages use it\n  - Skip — no implementation needed\n\n- `tree_formatter` (status: missing, action: implement) — 1 page: `admin/js/menus.js`\n  - EUI: enhanced formatter with cls wrapping and count badges\n  - DUI formatter supports iconCls and text but not cls wrapping or count badges\n  - Implementation: extend formatter to support `cls` property and `count` badge rendering\n  - Impact: behaviour_diff — tree renders but without visual enhancements"}
2026-03-09 10:05:12,886 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'form-plugin: reselect noop method', 'description': "Add `reselect` as a noop method to form-plugin. EUI pages call `$('#form').form('reselect')` to re-trigger the current combobox selection after save. In DUI, the form state machine + afterSave hook handles this pattern. The method must exist to prevent silent failure."}
2026-03-09 10:05:14,209 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'spinner-plugin: setValidType method', 'description': "Add `setValidType` method to spinner-plugin. One page (part_trans.js) calls `$('#el').numberspinner('setValidType', [...])` to dynamically change validation rules at runtime."}
2026-03-09 10:05:15,993 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'button-plugin: click debounce', 'description': 'Add click debounce to button-plugin to prevent double-submit on rapid clicks. EUI eui.extend.js overrides linkbutton click handler with a 300ms debounce. This is a global safety net — affects all buttons.'}
2026-03-09 10:05:17,649 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_new args={'title': 'migration-map: eui.table and eui.toolbar entries', 'description': 'Add migration-map.yaml entries for `eui.table()` → DUI datagrid pattern and `eui.toolbar()` → `toolbut()`. These are migrator hints, not runtime code — they guide the EUI→DUI migration script to produce correct output.'}
2026-03-09 10:05:28,956 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 21, 'text': "**form-plugin: reselect noop**\n\nYAML item: `form_reselect` (status: missing, action: shim_noop)\nPages: sa_parts.js, part_trans.js, capor_inc.js, woref.js, sa_jobman.js (5+ pages)\n\nEUI behaviour: `$('#head').form('reselect')` re-triggers the primary combobox's onSelect, which reloads the current record + child grids. Used after save to refresh data.\n\nDUI equivalent: The afterSave hook + form state machine already handles post-save refresh. Pages that need custom post-save behaviour use `$.page.register({ hooks: { afterSave: fn } })`.\n\nImplementation: Add `reselect` as a recognized method in form-plugin that is a noop (or optionally triggers afterLoad with current data). This prevents `TypeError` when migrated pages call it. Over time, pages should migrate to afterSave hooks.\n\nImpact: hard_error if missing — page calls method, gets undefined, may throw or silently fail to refresh."}
2026-03-09 10:05:32,797 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 22, 'text': "**spinner-plugin: setValidType**\n\nYAML item: `spinner_setValidType` (status: missing, action: implement)\nPages: inv/js/part_trans.js (1 page)\n\nEUI behaviour: `$('#QTY').numberspinner('setValidType', ['length[1,10]'])` — dynamically changes validation rules at runtime based on form state.\n\nDUI spinner-plugin currently has no setValidType. The validatebox-plugin has validation infrastructure.\n\nImplementation: Add `setValidType(rules)` method that updates the element's `data-options` validType and re-initializes validation. May delegate to validatebox-plugin internals.\n\nImpact: behaviour_diff — validation won't adapt dynamically, but form still works. Low priority."}
2026-03-09 10:05:38,348 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 23, 'text': "**button-plugin: click debounce**\n\nYAML item: `linkbutton_debounce` (status: missing, action: implement)\nPages: ALL buttons (global)\n\nEUI behaviour: eui.extend.js overrides `$.fn.linkbutton.defaults.onClick` with a 300ms debounce wrapper. Prevents double-submit on rapid clicks — critical for save/delete operations.\n\nDUI button-plugin has enable/disable/select/unselect but no debounce.\n\nImplementation: Add debounce to button click handling in button-plugin. Either:\n1. Wrap click handlers with 300ms debounce in the plugin init\n2. Add a `.debounce` class modifier that enables it selectively\n3. Apply globally to all `.btn` elements (matches EUI's global approach)\n\nOption 3 is safest — matches EUI behaviour exactly. Apply in button-plugin init or _startup.js.\n\nImpact: behaviour_diff without it — double-clicks can cause duplicate saves. Medium priority."}
2026-03-09 10:05:43,032 2155867 DEBUG mcpp.tool CALL plan_step_notes_set args={'number': 24, 'text': '**migration-map entries for eui.table and eui.toolbar**\n\nYAML items:\n- `eui_table` (status: not_needed, action: migration_map) — no DUI pages use it, but migrator needs pattern\n- `eui_toolbar` (status: not_needed, action: migration_map) — no DUI pages use it, but migrator needs pattern\n\nThese are NOT runtime implementations. They are entries in `yaml/migrator/migration-map.yaml` that tell the EUI→DUI migrator script how to transform these patterns:\n\n- `eui.table(selector, opts)` → DUI datagrid JSON config + `+datagrid` mixin\n- `eui.toolbar(buttons)` → `toolbut(buttons)` call inside `$.page.ready()`\n\nImplementation: Add pattern entries to migration-map.yaml with before/after examples.\n\nImpact: none at runtime — only affects future page migrations.'}
